						               													<description>L'&amp;eacute;chapp&amp;eacute;e Infernale: Race tactics and strategy&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Become sports manager and target your objectives according to your team (puncher, sprinter, climber) and the route (plain, hilly, medium and high mountain).&amp;#10;Set the record straight:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Jump on the right breakaway, The Infernal Breakaway, the one that will bring you to the finish line.&amp;#10;     Manage your energy capital as a great tactician:&amp;#10;     Here is the red flame of the last kilometer, already the finish line ... Start the sprint ... Watch out for falls ... victory will be played with one wheel ...&amp;#10;     Once you have crossed the finish line, it's time to do the math: Calculate the time of your runners and their places in the general classification. &amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;For this new edition, the game has been modernized: The old Cofalu riders have been replaced for some much more modern-looking specially designed for this game. The board has changed too. Now it features different sections for high mountain (red), medium mountain (pink), up-and-downs (yellow) and plain (blue).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rules have changed too. Now they are a little more complex. We have different kinds of riders (climber, sprinter, &amp;quot;puncheur&amp;quot;) and consequently we also have different types of terrains, four different types in fact (In the 2001 version of the game all riders were similar and there was only a climb in the board).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
